deck: Mike Diana is an underground comic artist in New York. He is well known for his book Boiled Angel, which was so grotesque that it led to him being the first comic book artist to ever be convicted of obscenity charges.
name: Mike Diana

description:
In January of 2000, Thor was involved in an automobile accident and suffered a cervical spinal cord injury, which left him paralyzed from the shoulders down. After months of rehab and physical therapy, he began acrylic painting and drawing by holding the brushes and pens in his jaws. Thor completed his first ten-page short story for Tellos: Maiden Voyage within a week of the one-year anniversary of his accident.

He has continued to work personally and professionaly since. Recent clients include Blizard Entertainment, Upper Deck Entertainment, Marvel Comics, and DC Comics.
name: Thor Badendyck

deck: Creator of the comic book "Turma da Mônica" (Monica's Gang) in Brazil. He is a great author in Latin America.
description:
Mauricio started out as a crime reporter at a newspaper, but he quit that job to become a comic book creator. He created Turma da Mônica, which was later translated into Monica's Gang. He drew the children from life, looking at his own children, he has ten, and thinking back on the children he knew when he himself was growing up.

The simple features of his characters made for easy adaptation into all kinds of merchandise. The gang is also featured on a myriad of products.
name: Mauricio de Sousa
